    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Tolumnia caymanensis improperly include developing skin irritation due to the plant's sap, which contains a toxic compound called calcium oxalate crystals that can cause irritation and inflammation on the skin. Experiencing allergic reactions is another potential side effect, as some people may be sensitive to the plant's sap or other compounds. Allergic reactions can range from mild to severe and may include symptoms such as hives, itching, and swelling. The plant's sap can also cause gastrointestinal issues, including diarrhea, in some individuals. These side effects can occur if the plant's sap comes into contact with the skin or is ingested accidentally, highlighting the importance of proper handling and precautions when working with Tolumnia caymanensis.",
