    "taxonomy": "Tolumnia caymanensis is a species of orchid. It is classified in the family Orchidaceae, which includes approximately 30,000 species of orchids. Within the family Orchidaceae, Tolumnia caymanensis is placed in the subfamily Epidendroideae. This subfamily is further divided into several tribes, with Tolumnia caymanensis likely belonging to the tribe Cymbidieae. However, a more specific classification within the tribe Cymbidieae would require further research.",
